{
  "id": "cleanorlabs/developer-reference-datasets",
  "title": "Developer Reference: Aspect, WCAG, MIME, Encoding",
  "subtitle": "Computed lookup tables: aspect-ratio pixels, WCAG contrast, UTF byte sizes",
  "description": "Open, reproducible reference data for web and app developers \u2014 computed from first principles, not scraped, so every value is exact and re-runnable.\n\n**What's inside**\n- **aspect-ratios.csv / resolutions.csv**: 16 named aspect ratios across 11 widths (16:9 at 1920 = 1080), and 29 named resolutions (720p to 8K, phones, social) with megapixels and reduced ratio.\n- **wcag-contrast-pairs.csv / wcag-on-white-black.csv**: WCAG 2.1 contrast ratio and AA/AAA pass-fail for every pair of a 25-colour UI palette, and each colour vs white and black.\n- **encoding-sizes.csv**: code points and UTF-8 / UTF-16 / UTF-32 byte sizes for 16 text samples across scripts (Latin 1 byte, CJK 3, emoji 4).\n\n**License:** CC BY 4.0 (attribution to Cleanor Labs).\n**Code & methodology:** https://github.com/cleanor-app/developer-reference-datasets\n**Write-ups:** https://cleanor.app/reference",
  "licenses": [
    {
      "name": "CC BY 4.0"
    }
  ],
  "keywords": [
    "computer science",
    "data analytics",
    "beginner",
    "tabular",
    "internet"
  ],
  "resources": [
    {
      "path": "aspect-ratios.csv",
      "description": "Named aspect ratios \u00d7 common widths \u2192 exact height.",
      "schema": {
        "fields": [
          {
            "name": "ratio",
            "description": "Aspect ratio label (e.g. 16:9)",
            "type": "string"
          },
          {
            "name": "ratio_w",
            "description": "Ratio width term",
            "type": "number"
          },
          {
            "name": "ratio_h",
            "description": "Ratio height term",
            "type": "number"
          },
          {
            "name": "ratio_decimal",
            "description": "Width/height as a decimal",
            "type": "number"
          },
          {
            "name": "orientation",
            "description": "landscape, portrait, or square",
            "type": "string"
          },
          {
            "name": "use_case",
            "description": "Where the ratio is commonly used",
            "type": "string"
          },
          {
            "name": "width_px",
            "description": "Width in pixels",
            "type": "number"
          },
          {
            "name": "height_px",
            "description": "Computed height in pixels",
            "type": "number"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
